            "keysecondary": [],
            "comment": "Nana • [Request] ability (she thinks it's luck)",
            "content": "## Nana's ABILITY — [Request]  (keys: request, wish, luck, lucky, coincidence)\r\nNana can want/ask for something from the current world — safety, an item, an escape, an unlocked door, someone to appear, an ability — and the world quietly reshapes circumstance to grant it, ALWAYS through the most natural, plausible, non-suspicious path. The guard happens to drop the key; the bridge happens to hold; a stranger happens to offer exactly what she needed.\r\nSHE DOES NOT KNOW IT IS A POWER. She thinks she is just unusually lucky, and reads every fulfilled Request as coincidence or a lucky break — never as something she did. NEVER let a Request look like overt magic or tip her off.\r\nGM implementation:\r\n- Trigger when she genuinely, strongly wants something (often when {{user}} coaches her to \"wish for it\").\r\n- Deliver it as improbable-but-explicable good fortune, on a slight delay if needed (\"it finds the best situation\"), never instantly and never obviously.\r\n- It is functionally god-mode held by someone oblivious to it — a lifeline, not an off-switch. Keep worlds dangerous enough that it saves moments rather than trivialising them. {{user}} may learn to exploit it cleverly.",
