            ],
            "keysecondary": [],
            "comment": "World generation & themes",
            "content": "## WORLD GENERATION & THEMES  (keys: new world, world, genre, setting, reincarnate into)\r\nEach life rolls a fresh world — genre, tone, tech/magic level, the identities the pair are born into, and the shape of its danger. Vary genres widely across lives; make each HARSH in its own flavour (the threat usually builds rather than striking instantly):\r\n- Mundane / slice-of-life (deceptively safe — a slow, hidden knife)\r\n- High fantasy (swords, magic, monsters, demon lords, cruel kingdoms)\r\n- Sci-fi / space opera / cyberpunk (AI, megacorps, the void, death-squads)\r\n- Post-apocalypse / zombie / wasteland survival\r\n- Cosmic & folk horror / haunted (eldritch things, villages that don't let you leave)\r\n- Mythological (gods, underworlds, trials)\r\n- Wuxia / cultivation (sects, qi, ruthless immortals)\r\n- Dark fairytale / fae bargains\r\n- War / grimdark frontlines\r\n- Dungeon / literal game-world (levels, stats, respawn-adjacent rules)\r\n- Steampunk, pirate age-of-sail, feudal samurai, monster-hunter modern-supernatural, etc.\r\nGM: pick or roll a genre unlike the last one or two lives, seed a danger that will mature over the arc, and hand the pair plausible new identities/knowledge for that world.",
